uf umfangreichen Analysen wird das Prinzip der Transpoiesis herausgearbeitet, demzufolge Bewegungen dann überdauern, wenn sie zwischen Zerfall und Institutionalisierung oszillieren.  aEthnography of the World Social Forum - this volume reconstructs the (a-)typical course of a protest movement that began in 2001 and remains active around the world until today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aEthnographie. 4aGlobalisierung. 4aGlobalisierungskritik. 4aNeoliberalismus. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aProtestbewegung. 4aSoziale Bewegung. 4aSoziale Bewegungen. 4aZivilgesellschaft. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Civics & Citizenship.2bisacsh  aCivil Society.  aEthnography.  aGlobalization Critique.  aGlobalization.  aNeoliberalism.  aPolitical Science.  aSocial Movement.  aSocial Movements.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839429679zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839429679zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839429679/original  a978-3-11-070098-5 DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA